    <h1 class="opener__hed  opener__hed--vertical-rule -is-over-bg opener__hed--light opener__hed--small" >        What’s Missing From Railroad Safety Data? Dead Workers and Severed Limbs.
    </h1>

    
            <div class="article-meta-1  -is-over-bg article-meta-1--light">
            <span class="article-meta-1__byline">
                by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/topher-sanders">Topher Sanders</a>, <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/dan-schwartz">Dan Schwartz</a>, <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/danelle-morton">Danelle Morton</a> and <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/gabriel-sandoval">Gabriel Sandoval</a>            </span>
            <time class="article-meta-1__pubdate">
                <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-03-13EDT05:00">March 13, 5 a.m. EDT</time>
            </time>
        </div>
    
    </div> <!-- Close .opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper -->

        <div class="content"> <!-- not sure if this is the best way to reestablish the text column -->
        <h2 class="opener__dek opener__dek--match-text-column" >            Thanks to government loopholes, rail companies haven’t been scrutinized by the Federal Railroad Administration for scores of alleged worker injuries and at least two deaths.
        </h2>
    </div>
    
</div>
        
<div class="article-meta-1
     article-meta-1--center      article-meta-1--hide-byline " data-pp-location="article meta">

    <span class="article-meta-1__byline" data-pp-location="article byine">
        by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/topher-sanders">Topher Sanders</a>, <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/dan-schwartz">Dan Schwartz</a>, <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/danelle-morton">Danelle Morton</a> and <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/gabriel-sandoval">Gabriel Sandoval</a>    </span>
    <time class="article-meta-1__pubdate">
        <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-03-13EDT05:00">March 13, 5 a.m. EDT</time>
    </time>

